organic_results.title: Analyzing distributions in school effects research: An empirical illustration
organic_results.snippet: This article presents a procedure for analyzing relationships involving distributions that is more informative about causal and other relationships than are analyses based on summary measures. First, the authors fitted a regression model to schools that participated in the 1980 High School and Beyond survey and found that the median test scores were affected negatively by the ratio of administrators to teachers and positively by two forms of specialization (personnel and facilities) and two dimensions of time devoted to schoolwork …
